                Senate
              </span> <span style="text-transform: uppercase">April 07, 2026</span><br/></td></tr></tbody><tbody><tr><td align="center"/></tr></tbody></table></div><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><font size="3" style="FONT-FAMILY: MinionPC, Arial Unicode MS">
                    CALIFORNIA LEGISLATURE—
                    2025–2026 REGULAR SESSION</font></div><br clear="all"/><span id="bill_house_num"><div style="float: left; width:50%; font-weight: bold; "><span style="text-transform: uppercase; text-align:left;width:50%;"><b>
                Senate Bill
              </b></span></div><div style="float:right; width:50%; text-align:right;"><span style="text-transform: uppercase;"><b>No. 1178</b></span></div></span><hr/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><table style="border-collapse: collapse" cellSpacing="0" align="center" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td id="bill_authors" align="center"><span style="font-weight:bold;">Introduced by Senator Reyes<br/></span></td></tr><tr><td id="bill_intro_date" align="center" class="textcenter"><br/>February 18, 2026</td></tr></tbody></table></div><hr/><br clear="all"/><div id="title"><span style="font-weight:normal;font-size:0.9em;"> An act to add<font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> and repeal</i></font> Section 425.17<font color="#B30000"><strike> to</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> of</i></font> the Government Code, relating to state government. </span></div><br clear="all"/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><h2>LEGISLATIVE COUNSEL'S DIGEST</h2></div><br/><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0"><span id="subject">SB 1178, as amended, Reyes.
                          <font color="#B30000"><strike>State wasp. </strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>California State Library: study: state wasp.</i></font></span></div><div><span id="digesttext"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Existing law establishes the state flag and the state’s emblems, including, among other things, the golden poppy as the official state flower, the California redwood as the official state tree, and the California Grizzly Bear as the official state animal.<font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> Existing law establishes the California State Library within the state government and vests control of the library to the State Librarian. Existing law authorizes the California State Library to serve as the central reference and research library for the departments of state government and maintain adequate legislative reference and research library services for the Legislature.</i></font></div><font color="#B30000"><strike><p style="display:inline;"><s>This bill would establish the California yellow jacket (Vespula sulphurea) as the official state wasp.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This bill would require the California State Library to conduct a study, in consultation with the public, on the best candidate for the official state wasp. The bill would require the California State Library, on or before January 1, 2028, to submit a report to the Legislature with the California State Library’s recommendations based on the study, as provided. The bill would repeal these provisions on January 1, 2032.</div></i></font></span></div><span class="hidden"><h2>Digest Key</h2></span><span id="vote">
      Vote:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">MAJORITY</span>  </span><span id="appropriation">
      Appropriation:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span><span id="fiscalcommittee">
      Fiscal Committee:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase"><font color="#B30000"><strike>NO</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>YES</i></font></span>  </span><span id="localprogram">
      Local Program:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span></div><hr/><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Text</h2></span><div id="bill"><div style=" text-transform: uppercase"><h2 style=" text-align: left;">The people of the State of California do enact as follows:</h2><br/></div><div id="s10.4291653727559025"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0" class="ActionLine"><h3 style="font-weight:bold; display:inline;"><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>SECTION 1.</i></font></h3> <font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>Section 425.17 is added to the Government Code, to read:</i></font></div><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i></i></font><div><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i><div id="id_FA5E2108-44E3-4A6E-BDA0-3658106E81B7"><div><p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><h6 style="display:inline;">425.17.</h6> (a) The California State Library shall conduct a study, in consultation with the public, on the best candidate for the official state wasp.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(b) (1) On or before January 1, 2028, the California State Library shall submit a report to the Legislature with the California State Library’s recommendations based on the study conducted pursuant to subdivision (a).</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(2) A report to be submitted pursuant to paragraph (1) shall be submitted in compliance with Section 9795.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(c) This section shall be repealed on January 1, 2032, pursuant to Section 10231.5.</div></p></div></div></i></font></div></div><font color="#B30000"><strike><caml:BillSection id="id_6B40D0E7-25C2-4BDE-852A-7EE81C7CAE7B"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>SECTION 1.</caml:Num><caml:Content><p style="display:inline;"><s>The Legislature hereby finds and declares all of the following:</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><p style="display:inline;"><s>(a)<span class="EnSpace"/>The California yellow jacket, or Vespula sulphurea, is native to California’s Upper Sonora region.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><p style="display:inline;"><s>(b)<span class="EnSpace"/>The California yellow jacket is not a common species. Known for its unique greenish-yellow “racing stripes,” it can be identified by the longitudinal bands across its thorax.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><p style="display:inline;"><s>(c)<span class="EnSpace"/>Like most yellow jacket species, their nests are built in underground nests and follow the typical hive system with a queen, drone, and workers that protect the colony.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><p style="display:inline;"><s>(d)<span class="EnSpace"/>Their diet consists of sugars from nectar, fruits, and plant sap, as well as proteins from other insects such as spiders, flies, and caterpillars. Yellow jackets also benefit gardeners and farmers by acting as natural pest control. These effective predators only eat live prey like beetles, caterpillars, and invasive fruit flies that damage crops.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><p style="display:inline;"><s>(e)<span class="EnSpace"/>Colton High School in the County of San Bernardino, which opened in 1895, has had the yellow jacket as the school mascot since the 1950s named Yogi. Several other schools across the state such as Berkeley High School and Franklin High School in Stockton also have the yellow jacket as the school mascot.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></caml:Content></caml:BillSection><caml:BillSection id="id_A2299BD9-5481-4B3D-829D-E999D15BACCD"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>SEC. 2.</caml:Num><caml:ActionLine action="IS_ADDED" xlink:href="urn:caml:codes:GOV:caml#xpointer(%2Fcaml%3ALawDoc%2Fcaml%3ACode%2F%2Fcaml%3ALawSection%5Bcaml%3ANum%3D'425.17'%5D)" xlink:label="fractionType: LAW_SECTION" xlink:type="locator">Section 425.17 is added to the <caml:DocName>Government Code</caml:DocName>, to read:</caml:ActionLine><caml:Fragment><caml:LawSection id="id_0DA7D839-2DF8-40B4-B1EF-E50E089B7892"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>425.17.</caml:Num><caml:LawSectionVersion id="id_C47FB2B6-BF8E-4D30-A4FC-5DC23109108E"><caml:Content><p style="display:inline;"><s>The California yellow jacket (Vespula sulphurea) is the official state wasp.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></caml:Content></caml:LawSectionVersion></caml:LawSection></caml:Fragment></caml:BillSection></strike></font></div></div></body></html>
